    <note>Cai(1) Chengxi [1645] His ancestors were Qiyang jun Cai(1). In the Tang, they moved to Changan. During the Southern Tang, they moved to Jiangning and then to Linchuan where they lived for six generations. His wife, He(2) Shi, was from an illustrious lineage (zhuzu) of Linjiang. His son-in-law, Fan(2) Shiji [3285], was Fan(2) Lingsun's [7025] great grandson or great grandnephew. Jiangxi TZ, 21.18a; XCB, 322.9a; Su Song, WJ, 57.9b-14a; Songshi yi, 2.3b. CBD, 5, 3815.</note>
